00:46:58.820 --> 00:47:04.130
even if we're not wise when we're old, umm,
and some people, you know, are wise

00:47:04.130 --> 00:47:08.370
beyond their years what have you but it didn't
 -- it certainly didn't take away

00:47:08.370 --> 00:47:12.240
any sort of elitist connotations when you
think about somebody who's very

00:47:12.240 --> 00:47:16.100
intelligent and you kind of put wisdom kind
of at the back and it was almost

00:47:16.100 --> 00:47:20.140
describing sort of a folksy sort of wisdom
which I don't necessarily agree with

00:47:20.140 --> 00:47:23.700
the things that neuroscientists or that you
had laid out as, like, sure, those

00:47:23.700 --> 00:47:26.040
are necessary but not sufficient.
Stephen: Mm hmm.

00:47:26.040 --> 00:47:29.220
&gt;&gt; Umm, but, you know, could you talk about
what influenced that approach and

00:47:29.220 --> 00:47:33.720
if there was kind of a sort of a populous
feel about it intentionally or if you

00:47:33.720 --> 00:47:36.910
just really wanted to throw it out there?
Stephen: I wouldn't call it populous but I

00:47:36.910 --> 00:47:43.040
would say -- I would frame it this
way. Umm, so much of intelligence is related

00:47:43.040 --> 00:47:47.490
to cog -- it has traditionally
been related to cognition, obviously, so sort

00:47:47.490 --> 00:47:52.430
of the cognitive part of
neuroscience has been focused on intelligence.

00:47:52.430 --> 00:47:56.870
The whole, umm, aspect of
emotional intelligence has really been something

00:47:56.870 --> 00:48:00.700
I'd say within the last 20
years or so, umm, this idea that there's other

00:48:00.700 --> 00:48:05.250
inputs, other forms of knowledge
and so forth. Umm, I think a lot of that has

00:48:05.250 --> 00:48:10.930
to do with negotiating the sort of
everyday dilemmas that people encounter and

00:48:10.930 --> 00:48:14.680
I think when people think about
wisdom or even Solomonic wisdom, the classic

00:48:14.680 --> 00:48:20.860
 -- the local story of Solomon, it's
resolving this very immediate dilemma in a

00:48:20.860 --> 00:48:26.650
very particular situation, how do you
do it? Umm, and so I think this emotional

00:48:26.650 --> 00:48:30.860
intelligence, this idea of emotional
intelligence, uh, this attentiveness to what

00:48:30.860 --> 00:48:34.280
emotion is doing in terms of
decision making and gathering information

00:48:34.280 --> 00:48:37.960
and so on is part of, uh, I think what
your you're talking about is something that

00:48:37.960 --> 00:48:44.470
everybody -- it doesn't require book
learning. It's more a -- a -- a learning kind

00:48:44.470 --> 00:48:48.231
of -- again, the control of this
emotional thermostat in a way which I think

00:48:48.231 --> 00:48:52.970
can be controlled with -- with, uh,
with use. I mean, the -- the -- the -- the

00:48:52.970 --> 00:48:58.020
big, umm, take home message from
neuroscience in the last ten or 15 years is

00:48:58.020 --> 00:49:02.630
this notion of plasticity, that
things change, umm, the brain changes on the

00:49:02.630 --> 00:49:07.710
basis of experience or what you do,
uh, and even how you exert yourself and these,

00:49:07.710 --> 00:49:11.340
uh, meditation experiments are
important because it shows that the brain

00:49:11.340 --> 00:49:15.390
is changing when you're doing this
repetitive mental exercise or making this

00:49:15.390 --> 00:49:20.740
mental exertion. Umm, I think what
that suggests is that even at the level of

00:49:20.740 --> 00:49:26.570
this emotional content that this can
be, umm, uh, at least modulated. I think we

00:49:26.570 --> 00:49:31.140
can learn to, you know, deal with
it at a certain level, modulate it, reduce

00:49:31.140 --> 00:49:36.970
the -- the impact of negative, uh,
events or adversity through this kind of concentrated

00:49:36.970 --> 00:49:41.030
practice and I really
think of it as, you know, if the 20 century

00:49:41.030 --> 00:49:45.980
 -- 20th century was a lot about
physical exertion and maintaining muscle tone

00:49:45.980 --> 00:49:49.531
in terms of deeming ourselves fit,
I think the 21st century is going to be about

00:49:49.531 --> 00:49:54.200
maintaining our mental tone by
mental exertion and really training our brains

00:49:54.200 --> 00:49:58.170
in terms of dealing with some of
these things. We're not there yet, I would

00:49:58.170 --> 00:50:01.211
hasten to add, clearly, but I think
it's really important.

