00:50:58.970 --> 00:51:04.180
experimentation in the book that suggests
that maybe an early moderate exposure

00:51:04.180 --> 00:51:10.620
to adversity or stress acts as a form of -- of
vaccination or inoculation where

00:51:10.620 --> 00:51:14.940
it seems to enable, at least in animal experiments,
it seems to enable these

00:51:14.940 --> 00:51:20.940
animals to deal -- deal with frustration and
difficult circumstances later on

00:51:20.940 --> 00:51:26.970
indeed and enhance their problem solving abilities
in these very specific tasks

00:51:26.970 --> 00:51:31.470
that they use in these experiments. Umm, I'm
certainly not suggesting that

00:51:31.470 --> 00:51:36.540
children should be deliberately placed in
adverse circumstances as a way of

00:51:36.540 --> 00:51:40.440
tuning this tissue but I think it's something
to be mindful of. There's a --

00:51:40.440 --> 00:51:46.060
there's a history, umm, in terms of the major
figures of both philosophy and

00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:52.990
religion, uh, of, umm, early life adversity
and people like Aristotle had a

00:51:52.990 --> 00:51:57.880
speech impediment, was orphaned; Mosas had
a speech impediments; umm, the

00:51:57.880 --> 00:52:02.260
